HEADWORD: Passegarde
<hw>Passe"garde`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Anc. Armor)</fld> <def>A ridge or projecting edge on a shoulder
piece to turn the blow of a lance or other weapon from the joint of the
armor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

